<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nA searing light comes over you, and suddenly the weight vanishes. You emerge from the sand, almost propeled by the pressure from above you. \n\nYou breathe in violently, and begin gasping desperately for more air. For a moment it seems that you have survived the sandy tomb, only to succumb to choking. After awhile you regain composure, but despite yourself you cannot keep from trembling.\n\nYour vision returns, but the outlook is grim. Still surrounded by sand, you watch as hail shoots up from the sand and transforms to stone before landing and resting on the ground. In the distance, you gaze at a tall tower, black and shimmering. A heat swells around you, and you feel your plectrum warming.\n\nYou attempt to stand, but find it is beyond you. The sight of the tower fills you with a dread you cannot describe. \n</center>\n</border>\nYou hesitantly log off, grateful for the ability to do so.
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou search the beach for any kind of shelter. You look behind you, but the storm veils any options. The flashing comes again, but dimmer now, as if very far away. Looming to your left is where the boardwalk should be, yet you see no sign of it. \n</center>\n</border>\n[[Head to the boardwalk|Stuck]]\n\n[[Go back|Stuck]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou raise a hand to your eyes to block the rain, and look out in the distance. You can make out the outline of a tall lighthouse, the same one from when you first arrived.\n\nWhile it seems like years since that confrontation on the boardwalk, your HUD informs you it's only been two months. The lighthouse remains firm against the storm, standing proud against the tall crashing waves.\n\nYou look back to Canassdra only to find that she's continued her march forward.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Catch up]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou are beaten. The sand squelches as it devours you, but you remain composed, accepting defeat with grace. As the sand rises to your neck, and the hail pounds the sand around you, you take one final breath before disappearing completely.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Hold]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou reach behind you and lay a hand on your stone Plectrum. Your heart sinks as the stone is cold to your touch. You'll have to wait until the storm passes to use your abilities.\n\nAnother flash comes, and you strive towards it. It seems as if it is drawing farther and farther away.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Seek shelter]]\n\n[[Continue seeking]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou start moving against the storm. The air chills you and you have trouble distinguishing the sound of the waves from the thunder that surrounds you.\n\nA wave collides with the shore with such intensity you have to leap to the side to avoid being caught in the undertow. You look over your shoulder to see a figure in the distance, far behind you. \n\nWithout fail, they just keep coming.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Find Canassdra]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou turn to go, but to your surprise you cannot move. You look down to see the sand sucking at your legs.\n\nYou strain with all your might to lift your feet from under the sand, but a greater force sucks them down deeper. The hail grows thicker, and begins pelting you, leaving welts and drawing blood.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Struggle]]\n\n[[Remain calm]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou stumble along the shore, the hail and rain mixed with the thunder and roaring waves obscures your sight and blots out your hearing.\n\nYour skin feels wet and raw under the assault, and you strain your eyes looking for each flash, constantly finding yourself stumbling away from it and having to scramble back towards it.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Grasp your Plectrum]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou look ahead to find Canassdra, but the torrent of rain thickens and your vision is severely hampered. \n\nYou consider calling out, but knowing that you wouldn't hear a response in return only maddens you. \n\nYou trudge on.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Gaze across the violent waves]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYour eyes shift across the waves, their crests glowing faintly red. The rain turns to hail as you search for the source of the red glow and for Canassdra. With arms raised you shield yourself from the storm.\n\nA light flashes, bright red in the distance. \n\nIt flashes again, almost calling you to come.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Go towards the red light]]\n\n[[Seek shelter]]\n

<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou stare out at the rolling sea, rain pouring down upon you as you trudge against the sand.\n\nCanassdra walks ahead, untouched by the downpour and unmoved by the howling wind.\n\nGreat waves rise in the distance, and come crashing down only a few feet from your side. The surf licks at your heels, and the blue tones of the sky and water turn a deep blue.\n\nCanassdra halts and points.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Stare out]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou fall to the sand and the hail falls on you like mighty blows from above. The sand swells under you, and you feel your body sinking in. With effort you pick yourself up, but falter again only a few more steps ahead.\n\nYou look and see the sand sucking at your feet as you rise once more. You lift a foot up from the sand, but your other foot sinks deeper. You try to plant your other foot on the sand, but it's of no use. The sand grasps your leg now, and some unseen force pulls your body into the beach. \n\nThe hail grows thicker, falling on you like a hammer driving a nail into the ground.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Struggle]]\n\n[[Remain calm]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nReluctantly you call out, straining to be heard over the storm and the sea. The flash comes again, but the silhouette seems no closer to you. \n\nThe sand continues to devour you as you scream for help. The hail pounds upon you, driving you deeper below. You see hail hit the sand and sink past it, like arrows through cloth.\n\nAs the sand begins to fill your gaping mouth, you take one final gasp of air before disappearing completely.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Hold]]
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou struggle in vain to free yourself from the devouring sands. You sink deeper and deeper, your body rapidly disappearing inch by inch.\n\nYou look for anything to grab hold of, any hope for rescue, or of Canassdra. The red flash comes again, this time from your far right, and in the distance, illuminated by the light, is the silhouette of the follower from before.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Call out]]\n\n[[Submit to the sands]]

<center style="border: 1px solid white">You feel the sand collapse around you, filling the pocket of space until you cannot move. You can see nothing, and hear only the beating of your heart. The thumping rises as your last breath aches in your lungs. \n</center>\n</border>\nIt occurs that you need only open your mouth and breathe the air inside your room. You attempt to do so, but the aching in your lungs refuses to be sated, and your body remains still, despite your willing it to move.<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nThe sand begins to apply pressure to you. A squeezing sensation comes from all sides, and your skin prickles under the force.\n</center>\n</border>\nYou feel a weight press down on you, as if your room truly is filled with sand. Again you attempt to move, or to breathe, but the effort seems suddenly beyond you. Your face begins to turn blue, and you dart your eyes, attempting to see past the console screen.<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYour heart's beating becomes as loud as the thunder on the beach. A great urge to vomit overtakes you, but you make only choking noises. The pressure on you builds, but now it comes from above, threatening to split your skull with it's force.\n</center>\n</border>\nWater pours from your eyes and you try to navigate to the log out screen. Your body refuses to comply, and your screen remains dark. You hear your heart subsiding to a whisper. Your fingers begin twitching of their own accord.<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nThe pressure continues to build, and you feel yourself moving, but yet, you cannot be sure as your mind begins racing. You feel spots appearing in your vision, but whether from the game or your eyes, you cannot distinguish. Your heart beats diminish to below a whisper. There is a great distance spanning before you. You cannot fathom it, yet you feel yourself plunging into it.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Emerge]]\n
<center style="border: 1px solid white">\nYou recognize your peril, and understand that you've been outmatched. The figue in the distance cannot save you, even if he was willing, nor can you save yourself.\n\nYou take a deep breath, and are swallowed completely by the sand.\n</center>\n</border>\n[[Hold]]
